2
00:03:16.160 --> 00:03:18.779
He slaughtered our men.

3
00:03:19.729 --> 00:03:22.208
our brothers.

4
00:03:23.568 --> 00:03:25.168
our sons.

5
00:03:26.847 --> 00:03:31.056
But they cry out to us for justice.

6
00:03:31.296 --> 00:03:35.425
For their souls. I swear to you

7
00:03:35.745 --> 00:03:38.613
the man who took our loved ones from us.

8
00:03:39.124 --> 00:03:43.103
the man who brought us such pain and sorrow.

9
00:03:44.483 --> 00:03:46.872
we will punish him.

10
00:03:47.242 --> 00:03:50.291
We will bring him... here.

11
00:03:51.021 --> 00:03:52.509
We'll not rest

12
00:03:52.530 --> 00:03:57.829
until his blood flows into this very ground.

13
00:03:59.109 --> 00:04:01.918
We will have our revenge.

14
00:04:22.902 --> 00:04:25.982
- Sir? Excuse me.
- Yeah.

15
00:04:26.401 --> 00:04:28.880
But the finish is included
in the cost of the wash.

16
00:04:28.921 --> 00:04:33.650
That's okay. I'd rather do it myself.
I'm a little obsessive that way.

17
00:05:15.658 --> 00:05:17.718
- Lenore.
- Bryan.

18
00:05:17.798 --> 00:05:20.447
- Hi. how are you?
- Fine. you?

19
00:05:20.477 --> 00:05:22.755
- Good. good.
- Somethin' up?

20
00:05:22.907 --> 00:05:27.196
No. It's Saturday. 2 o'clock.
Kim's driving lesson?

21
00:05:27.355 --> 00:05:29.026
Yeah. music lesson got switched.

22
00:05:29.135 --> 00:05:34.504
- The Tuesday one or the Friday one?
- I have no idea.

23
00:05:35.323 --> 00:05:36.310
You know how kids are.

24
00:05:36.433 --> 00:05:38.007
Um-huh! Especially those who're desperate

25
00:05:38.063 --> 00:05:40.337
to pass their driving test at their third try.

26
00:05:40.382 --> 00:05:41.302
She's not desperate.

27
00:05:41.382 --> 00:05:45.144
But she failed the test twice. Leny.
It's important.

28
00:05:45.721 --> 00:05:47.638
So ... where is she? Really.

29
00:05:50.299 --> 00:05:54.338
- I've never been a good liar. have I?
- No. it's not your forte.

30
00:05:55.768 --> 00:05:58.637
She met her boyfriend.

31
00:06:02.096 --> 00:06:04.006
She has a boyfriend?

32
00:06:04.066 --> 00:06:05.600
Do you want to come in for a drink?

33
00:06:06.535 --> 00:06:09.196
- Yeah.
- Yeah. I think you should. okay.

34
00:06:11.724 --> 00:06:13.581
Why didn’t she tell me. for God's sake?

35
00:06:13.653 --> 00:06:15.907
She probably didn't want
you running a full security

36
00:06:15.908 --> 00:06:18.161
check of everything thing
he's done since kindergarten.

37
00:06:22.651 --> 00:06:24.462
But she's okay. right?

38
00:06:24.980 --> 00:06:26.172
Yeah. she's okay.

39
00:06:31.955 --> 00:06:33.699
Tell me it's none of my business. but ...

40
00:06:34.610 --> 00:06:36.008
Are you okay?

41
00:06:38.894 --> 00:06:39.977
No.

42
00:06:41.136 --> 00:06:46.105
Not really. you know. we've separated.

43
00:06:46.864 --> 00:06:50.483
Well. is there nothing I can do?

44
00:06:51.543 --> 00:06:55.182
Well. I better... thanks for the wine.

45
00:06:55.712 --> 00:07:00.153
- Bryan! Don't.
- I don't even know where the kid lives.

46
00:07:00.171 --> 00:07:03.471
You found her in a city of
12 million people within 72 hours.

47
00:07:04.830 --> 00:07:06.359
- Promise me.
- I just told you...

48
00:07:06.409 --> 00:07:10.898
- Promise!
- I'm gonna give her her space.

49
00:07:49.668 --> 00:07:51.048
Hi.

50
00:07:52.147 --> 00:07:52.981
Can I help you?

51
00:07:56.385 --> 00:07:56.990
Is Kim here?

52
00:07:57.096 --> 00:07:59.119
- Yeah. and you are...?
- Her father.

53
00:07:59.895 --> 00:08:02.205
Mr. Mills. what a pleasure. I'm Jamie.

54
00:08:04.124 --> 00:08:04.956
Come in.

55
00:08:07.713 --> 00:08:10.988
- Can I get you anything? A drink or...
- Just my daughter would be fine.

56
00:08:12.202 --> 00:08:14.117
- Dad?
- Hi.

57
00:08:14.391 --> 00:08:15.461
What are you doing here?

58
00:08:15.521 --> 00:08:18.423
Well. I know how important it is
for you pass your tests.

59
00:08:18.600 --> 00:08:20.346
Wait! Kim you don't have a license.?

60
00:08:20.410 --> 00:08:22.218
Have you ever tried to parallel park an Escalade?

61
00:08:22.349 --> 00:08:24.634
I told you to take the test with my car.

62
00:08:25.298 --> 00:08:26.318
Dad.

63
00:08:29.817 --> 00:08:30.978
Thank you.

64
00:08:32.667 --> 00:08:34.219
It's a pleasure to meet you. Mr. Mills.

65
00:08:42.014 --> 00:08:45.283
Could we slow down a little bit. please.

66
00:08:45.453 --> 00:08:47.561
I can't believe you could do that.

67
00:08:47.763 --> 00:08:49.625
You're leaving in fall. right. next week.

68
00:08:49.672 --> 00:08:53.045
It's the only time I can get
to do this before I go to Istanbul.

69
00:08:53.061 --> 00:08:55.119
We planned this.
When you make plans. you keep them...

70
00:08:55.181 --> 00:08:56.901
No. Dad. you planned it.

71
00:08:57.640 --> 00:09:00.176
- How did you even find me?
- Your mom and I were talking...

72
00:09:00.239 --> 00:09:01.774
Why didn't you tell me you have a boyfriend?

73
00:09:01.849 --> 00:09:05.770
Because I knew you'd over-react and I just
wanted to be normal. even if I'm just pretending.

74
00:09:07.047 --> 00:09:09.350
- Remember to break before stop.
- Dad!

75
00:09:14.006 --> 00:09:16.053
Mom doesn't know where Jamie lives.

76
00:09:19.954 --> 00:09:20.961
GPS?

77
00:09:21.704 --> 00:09:23.846
I had it installed on your phone. I'm sorry.

78
00:09:23.943 --> 00:09:28.123
It's just... you hear so many scary stories
of goings-on of people your age.

79
00:09:28.192 --> 00:09:32.117
Dad. I don't even know how to start feeling
normal again. but this definitely isn't it.

80
00:09:34.491 --> 00:09:35.609
Kim. you can move.

81
00:09:49.206 --> 00:09:50.677
Use your side mirror.

82
00:10:03.363 --> 00:10:06.155
Perfect! Why couldn't you do that in the test?

83
00:10:07.422 --> 00:10:08.283
I don't know.

84
00:10:09.091 --> 00:10:12.232
Maybe I didn't really want a license.
Listen...

85
00:10:13.080 --> 00:10:14.463
Of course I know where you're coming from.

86
00:10:15.729 --> 00:10:17.725
But you gotta trust me to figure this out.

87
00:10:19.258 --> 00:10:22.372
- Don't do this again. please.
- I won't.

88
00:10:23.747 --> 00:10:26.786
And don't go running a background
check on him with your friend.

89
00:10:26.821 --> 00:10:27.903
I won't.

90
00:10:29.504 --> 00:10:30.354
Okay.

91
00:10:30.705 --> 00:10:34.731
- See ya Wednesday.
- Au revoir.

92
00:10:35.284 --> 00:10:38.066
- Love you.
- Hey. I love you.

93
00:11:10.865 --> 00:11:14.315
One moment.
A package came for you.

94
00:11:14.783 --> 00:11:17.485
I'll meet you inside.
As you wish. Sir.

95
00:11:20.862 --> 00:11:21.645
Your mail.

96
00:11:25.531 --> 00:11:26.741
Sebastian.

97
00:11:50.364 --> 00:11:53.466
- Where is he?
- I don't know.

98
00:11:56.766 --> 00:11:57.503
Okay.

99
00:12:02.961 --> 00:12:04.509
You want to play with me?

100
00:12:12.449 --> 00:12:14.923
But then. you could play her tomorrow.

9999
00:12:14.966 --> 00:12:14.967
