101
00:12:27.335 --> 00:12:30.098
- Look.
- No! No!

102
00:12:31.644 --> 00:12:35.078
Again the rules are changing.

103
00:13:19.251 --> 00:13:21.890
- What's happened? Are you okay?
- Yeah. no. I'm great.

104
00:13:21.970 --> 00:13:24.375
I'll... come in. I'll get Kim.

105
00:13:24.476 --> 00:13:25.569
Hey. hey.  hey. hey!

106
00:13:27.159 --> 00:13:29.403
- Leny. talk to me.
- We...

107
00:13:29.958 --> 00:13:33.565
We had this trip planned to
China for Kim's spring break...

108
00:13:33.566 --> 00:13:37.173
the family. you know. to
try and work things out.

109
00:13:37.476 --> 00:13:41.201
And when Stu and I... we thought
it'd be nice for Kim and I to...

110
00:13:41.202 --> 00:13:44.827
you know. to be away... together.
away from all the tension.

111
00:13:44.862 --> 00:13:48.195
- Sure.
- They cancelled everything. all the reservations.

112
00:13:48.913 --> 00:13:50.893
I just can't believe he did that to us.

113
00:13:55.331 --> 00:13:58.071
I'm tired of the fighting. the lawyers ...

114
00:13:58.881 --> 00:14:03.671
- He's turned into such a bastard.
- I'm sorry. Leny. I'm sorry.

115
00:14:05.679 --> 00:14:08.433
I'm sorry. this is really not your problem.

116
00:14:08.748 --> 00:14:12.944
It's my turn to have Kim for the fall.
I'll take care of that.

117
00:14:13.557 --> 00:14:16.884
Look. why don't you and
Kim come with me?

118
00:14:17.286 --> 00:14:21.032
But. we can't impose on you.
you're working.

119
00:14:21.045 --> 00:14:23.539
You're not imposing.
I'm working for 3 days.

120
00:14:23.614 --> 00:14:27.082
Then you could come over. it... could be fun.

121
00:14:27.403 --> 00:14:28.731
That's so sweet.

122
00:14:29.942 --> 00:14:32.202
I do not know. I... just...
I can't think of right now.

123
00:14:32.282 --> 00:14:34.400
Sure. I understand. I understand. no pressure.

124
00:14:35.011 --> 00:14:37.796
I leave in the morning.
I work three days. Call me.

125
00:14:37.880 --> 00:14:41.384
If you're coming. I'll hang around.
if not I'll come back. That's it.

126
00:14:41.739 --> 00:14:44.330
- I'll go get Kim.
- Okay.

127
00:14:44.359 --> 00:14:46.017
Thank you. Bryan.

128
00:14:56.385 --> 00:14:58.710
- She is definitely coming?
- I don't know.

129
00:14:58.805 --> 00:15:00.419
- Come on.
- Come on. Sam. I don't know.

130
00:15:00.474 --> 00:15:04.151
- You should have insisted.
- Come on. guys. cut me some slack.

131
00:15:04.213 --> 00:15:07.144
She's going through a hard time.
I didn't want to make it harder on her.

132
00:15:07.163 --> 00:15:09.256
- She was confiding in me.
- Oh!

133
00:15:09.352 --> 00:15:11.033
Well. I didn't know you guys
were still so cozy. that

134
00:15:11.132 --> 00:15:14.001
she shares her marriage issues with you.

135
00:15:14.321 --> 00:15:16.724
Wait a minute. I mean. I mean.
I know you guys were close. obviously

136
00:15:16.790 --> 00:15:20.409
but are you. like close again.
close like... you know?

137
00:15:20.544 --> 00:15:23.924
- Lay money she still got something for him.
- Don't got there. friend.

138
00:15:23.998 --> 00:15:26.336
- Whoa! Maybe he still has something for her.
- Well. that's...

139
00:15:26.387 --> 00:15:29.512
Could we talk about basketball.
for God's sake! Come on!

140
00:15:46.032 --> 00:15:47.733
Istanbul.

141
00:15:57.069 --> 00:15:58.256
Thank you. Mr. Mills.

142
00:15:58.899 --> 00:16:01.155
You made my stay feel very secure.

143
00:16:05.387 --> 00:16:07.274
Thank you. have a safe trip home.

144
00:16:07.497 --> 00:16:08.717
You also.

145
00:16:24.492 --> 00:16:27.075
You reached Lenore.
leave a message after the beep.

146
00:16:27.281 --> 00:16:28.635
Hey. it's me.

147
00:16:29.071 --> 00:16:30.231
No message from you

148
00:16:30.331 --> 00:16:32.940
so I guess probably found some place to go.

149
00:16:33.410 --> 00:16:35.599
I hope things are a little easier.

150
00:16:36.219 --> 00:16:39.168
If you ever need to talk
or anything. well. I'm here.

151
00:16:39.248 --> 00:16:40.728
I mean. I'll be there.

152
00:16:40.998 --> 00:16:43.207
I'll probably ship-out tomorrow.

153
00:16:43.697 --> 00:16:48.166
No news from Kim. so I guess
she's busy with the boyfriend. and all.

154
00:16:48.406 --> 00:16:49.546
Dad!

155
00:16:51.075 --> 00:16:54.004
- Surprise!
- My God. Kim. baby!

156
00:16:55.324 --> 00:16:57.204
- Hello. Leny.
- Hello. hi.

157
00:16:57.683 --> 00:17:00.453
I was just leaving you a message...
when I didn't hear...

158
00:17:00.733 --> 00:17:03.912
- We wanted to surprise you.
- Well. you succeeded.

159
00:17:04.652 --> 00:17:07.601
You guys could've been surprised.
I coulda been outta here and headed home.

160
00:17:07.691 --> 00:17:10.290
- Mom's been calling Sam.
- Oh yeah?

161
00:17:10.400 --> 00:17:11.956
- Uh-huh. yes
- We've been tracking YOU.

162
00:17:12.030 --> 00:17:14.699
Not exactly. you're not the only
one who's got moves. you know?

163
00:17:14.979 --> 00:17:18.148
Apparently not!
Welcome to Istanbul.

164
00:17:25.726 --> 00:17:28.608
- Not too shabby. huh?
- Wow!

165
00:17:29.265 --> 00:17:30.895
Oh. my God!

166
00:17:31.225 --> 00:17:33.554
Mom. Mom. look at this.

167
00:17:34.394 --> 00:17:37.153
- Oh my God!
- Crazy. right?

168
00:17:37.543 --> 00:17:39.682
- Thank you so much.
- My pleasure.

169
00:17:39.722 --> 00:17:43.731
But. listen. I'll let you get settled and I'll come
and collect you. in what. half an hour?

170
00:17:43.831 --> 00:17:45.382
Okay.

171
00:17:46.659 --> 00:17:47.474
Later.

172
00:18:16.443 --> 00:18:18.740
Pass.

173
00:18:54.133 --> 00:18:56.151
<i>The cause is still being investigated.</i>

174
00:18:56.262 --> 00:19:01.190
<i>but a source... actually in the area at
the time of Thursday's crash.</i>

175
00:19:01.191 --> 00:19:02.622
<i>on the island of Corsica.</i>

176
00:19:02.648 --> 00:19:06.903
<i>After the... made an unauthorized entrance
the ship then keeled over on its side.</i>

177
00:19:06.989 --> 00:19:08.239
- Hey.
- Hey.

178
00:19:08.499 --> 00:19:10.698
- You look great.
- You. too.

179
00:19:10.998 --> 00:19:13.358
So. where are we heading?

180
00:19:13.608 --> 00:19:16.713
Well. I am going nowhere. I'm beat.

181
00:19:16.747 --> 00:19:20.956
so I'm just gonna take a
nice. long bath and get into bed.

182
00:19:21.226 --> 00:19:23.915
- Leny. are you sure?
- Yeah.

183
00:19:24.595 --> 00:19:26.614
I guess it's just you and me. Kiddo.

184
00:19:32.293 --> 00:19:34.792
So. on this side is Europe

185
00:19:35.212 --> 00:19:38.241
and the other side is Asia.

186
00:19:39.571 --> 00:19:43.430
And every conquest since.
for the last 2 thousand 500 years

187
00:19:43.730 --> 00:19:46.559
whether it was the West going east
or the East going west.

188
00:19:46.859 --> 00:19:49.318
they all used this very same waterway.

189
00:19:50.488 --> 00:19:52.237
- Do you want tea. Babe?
- Yeah.

190
00:19:52.537 --> 00:19:54.017
Just one. please.

191
00:19:54.337 --> 00:19:55.996
So. how do you know all this stuff.

192
00:19:56.696 --> 00:20:00.385
How do I know? I read it in a book

193
00:20:01.165 --> 00:20:04.784
on the flight over.
And you can borrow it if you wish.

194
00:20:05.154 --> 00:20:06.414
Yeah. I would.

195
00:20:07.113 --> 00:20:09.633
So... uh... this...

196
00:20:10.313 --> 00:20:13.442
Jamie... is it... serious?

197
00:20:13.762 --> 00:20:16.011
I wasn't really ready for this transition.

198
00:20:18.780 --> 00:20:21.790
I don't know. it's only been a few months.

199
00:20:22.070 --> 00:20:23.969
Are you in love with him?

200
00:20:25.449 --> 00:20:27.568
I guess I'm not sure yet.

201
00:20:27.858 --> 00:20:32.477
- Have you ever been in love before?
- Not...

202
00:20:33.467 --> 00:20:36.466
Not the way that mom talks about it.

203
00:20:36.706 --> 00:20:38.205
How does she describe it?

204
00:20:38.595 --> 00:20:41.809
She said when you guys he met... that...

205
00:20:43.974 --> 00:20:46.573
- It was Super Special.
- Super Special.

206
00:20:46.823 --> 00:20:50.482
- She said that?
- I think the exact word she used was:

207
00:20:51.762 --> 00:20:53.291
Magical.

208
00:20:55.621 --> 00:20:57.230
Magical. huh?

209
00:21:39.119 --> 00:21:41.139
It is good to see you again. my friend.

210
00:21:43.818 --> 00:21:46.197
Is everything prepared?

211
00:21:46.597 --> 00:21:48.387
As you requested.

212
00:21:48.957 --> 00:21:50.226
Perfect.

213
00:22:35.014 --> 00:22:36.604
- Yeah?
- They're in the lobby.

214
00:22:36.884 --> 00:22:38.075
Wait until he's outside.

215
00:22:38.120 --> 00:22:40.353
<i>and remember... alive.</i>

216
00:22:42.662 --> 00:22:45.222
He's looking at me. I'm leaving.

217
00:23:01.947 --> 00:23:02.857
- Hey.
- Hi.

218
00:23:03.127 --> 00:23:04.887
I thought we were having lunch in the Bazaar.

219
00:23:06.136 --> 00:23:09.455
Jet lag just hit me so I figured
I'd veg-out at the pool

220
00:23:09.525 --> 00:23:12.894
and let you guys go and meet-up with you later.

221
00:23:12.984 --> 00:23:15.244
- I guess. okay with you?
- Okay. fine.

222
00:23:15.494 --> 00:23:16.304
Okay. bye.

223
00:23:16.584 --> 00:23:17.241
- Hey. Kim.
- Yeah.

224
00:23:17.513 --> 00:23:19.773
That book I was telling you about.
it's on my dresser.

225
00:23:20.602 --> 00:23:22.192
- Definitely.
- No adventure.

226
00:23:22.442 --> 00:23:24.241
- I’ll go call a car.
- Have fun.

227
00:23:24.961 --> 00:23:29.760
- Hey. Kim. I know what you're doing.
- What?

228
00:23:37.148 --> 00:23:38.168
Yeah?

229
00:23:38.518 --> 00:23:41.287
The daughter is still here so what can we do?

230
00:23:41.567 --> 00:23:43.316
I want all 3 of them.

231
00:23:44.986 --> 00:23:46.346
Yes.

232
00:23:48.545 --> 00:23:51.694
She thinks we just fell off the turnip truck.

233
00:23:51.964 --> 00:23:54.763
- What do you mean?
- She's trying to play Cupid.

234
00:23:55.053 --> 00:23:56.233
Oh. I see.

235
00:23:56.523 --> 00:23:58.422
You know? When you first
came back and said you

236
00:23:58.499 --> 00:24:00.768
wanted to make-up for all
the time you lost with Kim?

237
00:24:00.822 --> 00:24:04.191
- Uh-huh.
- Is that right! Three weeks he's gone.

238
00:24:04.491 --> 00:24:06.890
That was usually the full limit you stuck around.

239
00:24:07.200 --> 00:24:08.550
Give or take a week.

240
00:24:11.961 --> 00:24:12.879
We're too close.

241
00:24:13.199 --> 00:24:16.228
You really proved me wrong.
I thought you'd never change.

242
00:24:16.488 --> 00:24:19.807
- Why not?
- Ah... you're personality.

243
00:24:20.067 --> 00:24:21.956
You know. when you commit to something. ya gotta

244
00:24:23.006 --> 00:24:25.985
focus all your energy there.
like a dog with a bone.

245
00:24:26.245 --> 00:24:27.535
Nice analogy.

246
00:24:28.305 --> 00:24:30.004
You know what I mean.

247
00:24:30.264 --> 00:24:33.673
When you give. it's 100 percent of 100 percent.

248
00:24:33.953 --> 00:24:36.572
If I was on to something. it was just that thing.

249
00:24:36.962 --> 00:24:39.642
even though I tell myself something should change.

250
00:24:39.952 --> 00:24:41.581
I can never give it up.

251
00:24:43.201 --> 00:24:47.010
- You gave us up.
- No. never.

252
00:24:47.410 --> 00:24:48.619
Not in here.

253
00:25:05.975 --> 00:25:08.534
Driver. turn left.

254
00:25:11.903 --> 00:25:13.623
Leny. don't.

255
00:25:15.602 --> 00:25:16.522
What?

256
00:25:20.701 --> 00:25:23.570
- Will you tell me what's going on?
- It's okay.

257
00:25:29.918 --> 00:25:31.278
Move!

258
00:25:35.637 --> 00:25:38.096
See the gallery entrenched in
the middle of the block?

259
00:25:38.356 --> 00:25:40.316
- Will you tell me what's going on?
- Do you see it?

260
00:25:40.586 --> 00:25:41.785
Yeah. yeah. yeah. I see it.

261
00:25:41.865 --> 00:25:44.000
When we stop. I want you to get out of the car.

262
00:25:44.095 --> 00:25:46.554
While you're a shopper I want you to get inside.

263
00:25:46.854 --> 00:25:48.334
Okay. but will you tell me what's going on!

264
00:25:48.483 --> 00:25:49.233
- Listen to me!
- Tell me what's happening!

265
00:25:49.463 --> 00:25:50.583
Listen. Leny! There's no time for this!

266
00:25:50.833 --> 00:25:52.612
- Please talk to me!
- Listen!

267
00:25:52.662 --> 00:25:55.482
At the lights at the back of the
fabric store. turn right.

268
00:25:55.722 --> 00:25:59.071
Take the first street on the right.
and then left on the very next street.

269
00:25:59.111 --> 00:26:01.650
Go straight until you come to a set of steps.

270
00:26:01.980 --> 00:26:04.579
There's a red corridor. It's a lane.

271
00:26:04.999 --> 00:26:08.248
When you exit the lane.
there's a cab stand.

272
00:26:08.308 --> 00:26:12.017
Go back to the hotel. get Kim.
get the head of hotel security

273
00:26:12.267 --> 00:26:14.827
and demand they cordon-off your room.

274
00:26:15.106 --> 00:26:16.986
Do not open the door for anyone.

275
00:26:17.336 --> 00:26:19.615
No room service.
no police. no one!

276
00:26:19.675 --> 00:26:21.885
- You wait for me.
- I can't believe this is happening.

277
00:26:21.955 --> 00:26:23.544
I need you to focus.

278
00:26:26.563 --> 00:26:28.583
- Are you ready?
- No.

279
00:26:28.843 --> 00:26:31.492
Leny. I need you to be ready.
I need you to be ready!

280
00:26:31.732 --> 00:26:33.971
Come on. focus.
Driver! Stop!

281
00:26:35.901 --> 00:26:38.610
- Okay. go.
- Wait. what about you?

282
00:26:38.840 --> 00:26:39.730
I'll be fine.

283
00:26:40.010 --> 00:26:42.019
The guys following us are about to have a problem.

284
00:26:42.339 --> 00:26:43.748
When the dog has a bone.

285
00:26:44.722 --> 00:26:46.807
the last thing you want to
do is try to take it from him.

286
00:26:52.577 --> 00:26:53.926
Be careful.

287
00:26:57.255 --> 00:26:58.235
Out of the car.

288
00:26:58.965 --> 00:27:00.584
Come on!
Move. move. move!

289
00:27:04.733 --> 00:27:05.973
Sir! Please!

290
00:27:07.293 --> 00:27:09.022
Please. Sir!

291
00:27:12.561 --> 00:27:13.441
He knows.

292
00:27:14.051 --> 00:27:15.391
Do it now.

293
00:27:34.855 --> 00:27:35.545
Come on!

294
00:27:57.349 --> 00:27:58.139
Shit!

295
00:28:11.696 --> 00:28:13.745
Come on. Kim.
answer the God damn phone!

296
00:29:16.119 --> 00:29:17.218
God. no!

297
00:29:17.518 --> 00:29:21.357
Somebody help me!
The key! Open the door! Please!

298
00:29:22.407 --> 00:29:23.697
Shit!

299
00:31:19.756 --> 00:31:21.396
I'll blow his brains out.

300
00:31:27.244 --> 00:31:28.634
Bryan!

301
00:31:30.133 --> 00:31:33.403
- Please.
- Drop the gun.

302
00:31:37.002 --> 00:31:39.351
- I really wish you were here.
- Me too.

303
00:31:39.921 --> 00:31:41.400
<i>You have no idea.</i>

304
00:31:42.400 --> 00:31:44.989
<i>- What?
- My dad's calling.</i>

305
00:31:45.249 --> 00:31:46.479
<i>he's on a date with my mom.</i>

306
00:31:49.204 --> 00:31:49.878
Don't go away.

307
00:31:49.879 --> 00:31:51.688
<i>I miss you.</i>

308
00:31:54.867 --> 00:31:58.016
- How's it going?
- Listen to me carefully. Kim.

309
00:31:59.326 --> 00:32:04.344
Your mother...
and I... are going to be taken.

310
00:32:05.323 --> 00:32:06.157
Daddy!

311
00:32:06.498 --> 00:32:07.826
Oh. my God.

312
00:32:08.033 --> 00:32:09.963
People are going to come for you. too.

313
00:32:10.293 --> 00:32:12.702
<i>Leave the place where you are. call me.</i>

314
00:32:13.042 --> 00:32:14.822
<i>Go to where the book is I told you about.</i>

315
00:32:15.142 --> 00:32:17.381
There's the door. Go into the room

316
00:32:17.651 --> 00:32:19.780
and hide in the closet. You got that?

317
00:32:20.070 --> 00:32:22.770
- Yeah.
- Good. I'll call you.

318
00:32:23.029 --> 00:32:24.369
Go... now!

319
00:32:39.385 --> 00:32:40.395
No!

320
00:33:08.857 --> 00:33:10.977
She is in room 4-22.

321
00:33:27.892 --> 00:33:29.302
1. 2.

322
00:33:29.802 --> 00:33:33.041
3. 4. 5. 6...

323
00:33:35.430 --> 00:33:36.510
Right turn...

324
00:33:39.179 --> 00:33:41.279
Men singing...

325
00:33:52.336 --> 00:33:55.165
1. 2. 3...

326
00:33:57.904 --> 00:34:01.743
4. boat...

327
00:34:10.451 --> 00:34:11.881
The pool.

328
00:34:22.228 --> 00:34:24.627
Security. 4th floor. Can you hear me?

329
00:34:25.157 --> 00:34:26.757
Send someone now.

330
00:34:27.117 --> 00:34:31.366
25. 26. 27...

331
00:34:32.345 --> 00:34:37.194
28. 29. stop.

332
00:35:16.474 --> 00:35:18.043
Hammer on metal.

333
00:35:30.710 --> 00:35:33.169
Left. gear shift to second.

334
00:35:33.449 --> 00:35:36.488
1. 2. 3...

335
00:35:37.988 --> 00:35:39.468
Birds.

336
00:35:55.923 --> 00:35:58.063
Take them to the shop... straight.

337
00:36:39.192 --> 00:36:41.101
Right turn. 27.

338
00:36:44.630 --> 00:36:45.820
Then stop.

339
00:39:12.462 --> 00:39:14.291
Come on. Sam. pick up.

340
00:39:15.391 --> 00:39:18.220
Hey. this is Sam. leave me a message.

341
00:39:18.580 --> 00:39:19.940
Shit.

342
00:39:27.288 --> 00:39:29.867
- Are you guys okay?
- No. no.

343
00:39:30.197 --> 00:39:32.646
- Are you all right?
- Yes

344
00:39:33.166 --> 00:39:37.845
- I'm just scared.
- Kim. listen to me very carefully.

345
00:39:38.785 --> 00:39:41.654
I need you to calm down
and pull yourself together.

346
00:39:42.574 --> 00:39:45.563
The men who came for you. did they leave?

347
00:39:45.843 --> 00:39:47.662
Yes. what did they want?

348
00:39:48.112 --> 00:39:52.961
- I'm going to find out.
- Is Mom okay?

349
00:39:54.390 --> 00:39:57.530
- Dad?
- Mom's fine.

350
00:39:57.830 --> 00:39:59.719
<i>Good.</i>

351
00:39:59.959 --> 00:40:01.459
What are we gonna do?

352
00:40:01.739 --> 00:40:03.758
I want you to go to the U.S. embassy.

353
00:40:04.038 --> 00:40:06.617
- You'll be safe there.
- What about you and Mom?

354
00:40:08.207 --> 00:40:10.126
I'll figure something out.

355
00:40:11.396 --> 00:40:14.965
- Where are you now?
- I don't really know. Kim.

356
00:40:15.435 --> 00:40:17.464
<i>Dad. how can I tell them where to find you. then?</i>

357
00:40:17.774 --> 00:40:19.514
You can't. Now get going.

358
00:40:19.914 --> 00:40:21.871
- No.
- Kimmy.

359
00:40:21.983 --> 00:40:25.912
- No. tell me what to do.
- No. Kim.

360
00:40:26.162 --> 00:40:27.982
Dad. if you tell me what to do. I can do it.

361
00:40:28.282 --> 00:40:30.671
- Kim. this is not a game.
- I know that.

362
00:40:30.921 --> 00:40:32.500
It’s my parents' lives.

363
00:40:32.860 --> 00:40:34.280
<i>Dad. please.</i>

364
00:40:34.670 --> 00:40:36.359
<i>you're wasting time.</i>

365
00:40:41.138 --> 00:40:42.328
<i>Please.</i>

366
00:40:42.608 --> 00:40:44.097
tell me what to do.

367
00:40:45.447 --> 00:40:48.676
Can you get out of the closet safely?

368
00:40:53.445 --> 00:40:54.805
Yes

369
00:40:55.204 --> 00:40:58.024
If you can. take the case with you.

370
00:40:59.723 --> 00:41:00.609
Okay.

371
00:41:11.150 --> 00:41:13.310
- I'm aff!
- The combination is:

372
00:41:13.630 --> 00:41:16.919
2-3. 2-8. 8-4.

373
00:41:24.707 --> 00:41:25.386
<i>It is open?</i>

374
00:41:25.387 --> 00:41:26.066
Yes!

375
00:41:26.306 --> 00:41:28.526
- Okay. do you see a map?
- Yeah.

376
00:41:28.776 --> 00:41:31.342
Take the map. you'll see a scale

377
00:41:31.377 --> 00:41:32.814
<i>on the top in kilometers.</i>

378
00:41:33.244 --> 00:41:34.280
<i>Do you see it?</i>

379
00:41:35.786 --> 00:41:37.525
Yeah. I see it.

380
00:41:37.560 --> 00:41:39.983
Take a shoelace from one
of my shoes in the closet.

381
00:41:40.412 --> 00:41:42.452
<i>Use it as a guide.</i>

382
00:41:45.041 --> 00:41:48.840
<i>There's a pen in the case. take it.</i>

383
00:41:49.090 --> 00:41:49.663
<i>Draw a circle</i>

384
00:41:49.691 --> 00:41:51.490
with the hotel in the center of it.

385
00:41:53.799 --> 00:41:54.517
It's done!

386
00:41:54.679 --> 00:41:55.484
Make the diameter

387
00:41:55.545 --> 00:41:58.608
<i>3 kilometers. You got that?</i>

388
00:42:07.135 --> 00:42:07.808
<i>It's done!</i>

389
00:42:07.845 --> 00:42:10.285
Draw another circle with the market in the center.

390
00:42:12.963 --> 00:42:13.646
<i>Okay!</i>

391
00:42:13.681 --> 00:42:14.156
Do the circles

392
00:42:14.198 --> 00:42:15.313
<i>intersect at any point?</i>

393
00:42:15.903 --> 00:42:16.953
<i>No.</i>

394
00:42:18.562 --> 00:42:20.962
Now take one of those little cans.

395
00:42:21.042 --> 00:42:22.651
<i>The ones with the pins on the top.</i>

396
00:42:22.911 --> 00:42:23.844
<i>It's a grenade. I want you to</i>

397
00:42:23.907 --> 00:42:26.100
go to the balcony with the grenade.

398
00:42:27.940 --> 00:42:30.349
Is there a safe place you can throw it?

399
00:42:34.128 --> 00:42:36.628
- There’s a parking garage.
- Anyone on it?

400
00:42:37.397 --> 00:42:40.177
- No.
- I want you to pull the pin out of the grenade.

401
00:42:40.457 --> 00:42:41.616
count to 3 so that I can hear it.

402
00:42:41.856 --> 00:42:43.606
and toss it as far as you can.

403
00:42:43.886 --> 00:42:45.168
<i>Then run back into the room.</i>

404
00:42:45.426 --> 00:42:48.165
keep the phone on so
I hear the explosion.

405
00:42:50.754 --> 00:42:54.193
1. 2. 3.

406
00:43:02.641 --> 00:43:06.433
1. 2. 3. 4.

407
00:43:09.359 --> 00:43:11.908
- Dad?
- Now draw a circle on the map.

408
00:43:12.268 --> 00:43:13.716
<i>Put the hotel on the mid-line</i>

409
00:43:13.814 --> 00:43:17.357
and the circumference
at 4 point 5 kilometers.

410
00:43:23.954 --> 00:43:24.692
<i>Okay.</i>

411
00:43:24.727 --> 00:43:27.624
Do the circles intersect at any point?

412
00:43:27.854 --> 00:43:29.064
Yes. two points.

413
00:43:29.304 --> 00:43:31.413
I'm at one of the two intersecting points.

414
00:43:31.683 --> 00:43:32.694
<i>Now. go outside and</i>

415
00:43:32.794 --> 00:43:34.502
look at the flags on the rooftops.

416
00:43:35.602 --> 00:43:37.152
<i>Do you see the flags?</i>

417
00:43:38.951 --> 00:43:41.371
- Yes
- Are they in the wind?

418
00:43:41.950 --> 00:43:44.770
- Yes
- Going east. right?

419
00:43:46.059 --> 00:43:47.669
I think so. yeah. how do you know?

420
00:43:47.919 --> 00:43:48.899
Now look at the map.

421
00:43:49.259 --> 00:43:50.462
I want you to go to the point

422
00:43:50.681 --> 00:43:52.902
<i>where the circles intersect at the east.</i>

423
00:43:53.277 --> 00:43:54.777
I want you to take one of the guns.

424
00:43:55.057 --> 00:43:56.447
get to a rooftop. wait for my call.

425
00:43:56.727 --> 00:44:02.025
And two of the grenades. You go to the
rooftop at the most easterly point.

426
00:44:03.065 --> 00:44:05.934
Get up to the rooftop. wait for my call.

427
00:44:06.354 --> 00:44:09.493
Be casual. Kim.
blend in.

428
00:44:09.494 --> 00:44:10.606
Okay.

429
00:44:13.072 --> 00:44:13.922
Dad?

430
00:44:16.291 --> 00:44:17.601
Dad?

431
00:45:05.967 --> 00:45:07.554
What are you doing?

432
00:45:07.768 --> 00:45:14.417
This is an employees' locker room!
Wait! Stop!

433
00:45:45.258 --> 00:45:47.367
Do you know this man?

434
00:45:53.456 --> 00:45:54.955
This one?

435
00:45:56.615 --> 00:45:59.474
- This one?
- No.

436
00:46:00.994 --> 00:46:02.413
This one?

437
00:46:03.713 --> 00:46:06.562
- What do you want?
- You recognize none of them.

438
00:46:06.822 --> 00:46:12.597
To you they were nothing. but to
other people they are... sons.

439
00:46:13.091 --> 00:46:15.270
and grandsons.

440
00:46:15.620 --> 00:46:19.779
fathers and husbands.
And you killed them all.

441
00:46:21.358 --> 00:46:23.708
Like they were so many nothings.

442
00:46:30.536 --> 00:46:32.166
And this one?

443
00:46:33.805 --> 00:46:35.455
Do you recognize him?

444
00:46:35.865 --> 00:46:38.254
You DO recognize him.

445
00:46:38.584 --> 00:46:41.943
And you didn't just kill him.
you strapped him to a chair.

446
00:46:42.273 --> 00:46:45.012
you touched electric cables to the chair

447
00:46:45.112 --> 00:46:46.690
you turned the current on.

448
00:46:46.712 --> 00:46:50.671
and you left it on until his heart burst.

449
00:46:50.991 --> 00:46:53.600
He's the one who kidnapped dozens of girls

450
00:46:53.880 --> 00:46:55.180
and ruined their lives.

451
00:46:55.519 --> 00:46:59.018
He was my son. Marko

452
00:46:59.888 --> 00:47:01.838
From Trepoja.

453
00:47:02.478 --> 00:47:06.477
And I have come to take you to Trepoja

454
00:47:06.836 --> 00:47:10.435
to face you to the people
whose lives you ruined.

455
00:47:10.705 --> 00:47:13.785
- To give them justice.
- You mean to give them their revenge.

456
00:47:14.045 --> 00:47:17.614
Because it gives us peace.
call it anything you wish.

457
00:47:18.083 --> 00:47:21.663
I killed your son because
he kidnapped my daughter!

458
00:47:24.012 --> 00:47:25.505
I don't care what he did!

459
00:47:27.744 --> 00:47:28.950
I will know...

460
00:47:29.692 --> 00:47:32.640
I will never see his face again.

461
00:47:32.990 --> 00:47:35.549
I will never hear his voice.

462
00:47:40.847 --> 00:47:44.027
And if you held him responsible
for your daughter.

463
00:47:44.107 --> 00:47:46.226
I hold YOU responsible for him.

464
00:47:47.556 --> 00:47:51.845
Your death will not be quick.
it will not be pleasant.

465
00:47:52.114 --> 00:47:54.994
But before you die. this is what you'll see.

466
00:48:33.214 --> 00:48:36.833
How long will it take for
the blood to rush to her head

467
00:48:37.253 --> 00:48:39.132
and have no place to go?

468
00:48:41.591 --> 00:48:45.370
- About 30 minutes.
- You are right.

469
00:48:45.470 --> 00:48:49.639
You are next for this.
so you have 30 minutes to watch her die.

470
00:48:49.939 --> 00:48:51.669
She had nothing to do with this.

471
00:48:52.449 --> 00:48:54.758
Do what you want with me. let her go.

472
00:48:54.818 --> 00:48:56.558
Don't play the hero with me.

473
00:48:56.827 --> 00:48:58.647
Now we're going to get your daughter.

474
00:48:58.687 --> 00:49:02.176
She will be sold to the
lowest brothel in this world.

475
00:49:03.186 --> 00:49:06.065
She will be abused by so many men.

476
00:49:06.215 --> 00:49:09.584
for she'll be nothing more than a piece of meat

477
00:49:09.944 --> 00:49:11.783
that a dog would not have.

478
00:49:26.790 --> 00:49:28.189
Don't listen to them. Leny.

479
00:49:28.869 --> 00:49:31.578
Kim is safe. I talked to her.

480
00:49:31.848 --> 00:49:33.128
She's safe.

481
00:49:33.418 --> 00:49:35.157
You have to stay calm.

482
00:49:35.427 --> 00:49:37.157
Breathe slowly. you have to.

483
00:49:37.447 --> 00:49:40.416
I won't let anything happen to you.
or to her... I promise.

484
00:49:47.864 --> 00:49:48.737
Quiet!

485
00:49:48.994 --> 00:49:50.753
We lost the girl.

486
00:49:51.643 --> 00:49:54.182
The girl has gone.
I'll be back as soon as we get her.

487
00:49:54.492 --> 00:49:56.172
Then we move. let's go!

488
00:49:57.621 --> 00:49:59.301
Hold on. Leny.

489
00:50:21.105 --> 00:50:23.265
Hold on. Leny. hold on.

490
00:50:34.732 --> 00:50:36.061
Sorry!

491
00:50:41.560 --> 00:50:42.407
Leny!

492
00:50:44.188 --> 00:50:45.413
Leny!

493
00:50:54.366 --> 00:50:57.016
I put your things down here. I'm here.

494
00:51:21.409 --> 00:51:23.429
Come on. call!

495
00:51:24.299 --> 00:51:25.042
Please.

496
00:51:30.267 --> 00:51:33.676
Leny. I'm coming back.

497
00:51:46.113 --> 00:51:48.482
- I'm here.
- Set-off another grenade.

498
00:52:02.968 --> 00:52:04.868
- Dad
- You're close.

499
00:52:05.088 --> 00:52:07.177
<i>I want to keep moving east.</i>

500
00:52:07.537 --> 00:52:08.689
Count to 30

501
00:52:08.698 --> 00:52:09.857
<i>and then set-off another one.</i>

502
00:52:10.136 --> 00:52:12.726
1. 2. 3...

503
00:52:16.675 --> 00:52:18.464
18. 19...

504
00:52:21.653 --> 00:52:26.102
27. 28. 29. 30.

505
00:52:32.860 --> 00:52:34.400
Go out and check what's going on.

506
00:52:41.858 --> 00:52:42.833
Kim.

507
00:52:42.834 --> 00:52:43.808
<i>Yeah?</i>

508
00:52:44.108 --> 00:52:45.642
Look east!

509
00:52:45.643 --> 00:52:47.177
<i>Look for a white cloud of steam!</i>

510
00:52:49.416 --> 00:52:50.916
- I see it!
- Run for it.

511
00:52:51.166 --> 00:52:52.565
tell me when you're there.

512
00:52:54.925 --> 00:52:56.294
I'm going down.

513
00:53:13.100 --> 00:53:14.679
- Dad
- Where are you?

514
00:53:14.959 --> 00:53:16.131
I'm right by the steam.

515
00:53:16.280 --> 00:53:18.199
<i>Drop the gun down the vent.</i>

516
00:53:18.468 --> 00:53:20.928
- Those guys are here. they're coming.
- Drop the gun. Kim.

517
00:53:21.348 --> 00:53:23.241
and run!

518
00:53:24.197 --> 00:53:25.567
Go!

519
00:53:25.568 --> 00:53:27.336
<i>Dad. they're coming!</i>

520
00:54:00.587 --> 00:54:02.157
I'll be back.

521
00:54:28.100 --> 00:54:30.360
Hey. what are you doing in the hall?

522
00:55:40.804 --> 00:55:41.181
Drop it!

523
00:55:44.090 --> 00:55:45.570
On your knees!

524
00:55:49.079 --> 00:55:51.288
Don't do this.

525
00:56:03.255 --> 00:56:04.225
Dad!

526
00:56:04.905 --> 00:56:08.174
Dad! Dad!

527
00:56:14.312 --> 00:56:16.022
Where's Mom? Is she okay?

528
00:56:16.062 --> 00:56:18.571
She's safe. she's safe.

529
00:56:28.878 --> 00:56:30.438
Slow down. slow down. slow down.

530
00:56:50.543 --> 00:56:53.102
That man had the same
tattoo as the men in Paris.

531
00:56:53.352 --> 00:56:55.740
It's not you they want
Kim. it's me.

532
00:57:10.787 --> 00:57:13.476
I want you to wait here.
I'm going to get mom.

533
00:57:13.636 --> 00:57:18.155
Wait five minutes and if I don't show up.
I want you to go straight here:

534
00:57:18.455 --> 00:57:19.775
The American embassy.

535
00:57:20.145 --> 00:57:22.014
- Tell them what happened.
- Dad.

536
00:57:22.254 --> 00:57:23.944
No time. Kim. give me your phone.

537
00:57:24.004 --> 00:57:26.513
You wait five minutes. not a moment longer.

538
00:57:26.813 --> 00:57:31.072
No matter what happens. time runs out.
you go! You understand me?

539
00:57:31.872 --> 00:57:32.911
Okay.

540
00:59:06.667 --> 00:59:07.966
- Let me go.

541
00:59:13.505 --> 00:59:14.465
Please.

542
00:59:34.479 --> 00:59:35.359
Yes?

543
01:00:01.232 --> 01:00:02.602
- Move!
- You killed him.

544
01:00:02.832 --> 01:00:03.932
I had no choice. now move.

545
01:00:04.211 --> 01:00:06.241
- Where's Mom?
- She's fine. she's not far.

546
01:00:06.481 --> 01:00:08.690
- Where is she?
- Come on. Kim. move!

547
01:00:10.280 --> 01:00:11.849
- I don't wanna do this.
- Go on. Kim.

548
01:00:12.079 --> 01:00:13.579
- Where are we going?
- Go straight!

549
01:00:13.609 --> 01:00:15.229
We have to go to the embassy.

550
01:00:17.818 --> 01:00:20.777
- I'm not sure I can.
- You know how to shoot?

551
01:00:21.027 --> 01:00:22.687
- No.
- Then drive.

552
01:00:30.095 --> 01:00:31.154
They escaped.

553
01:00:37.083 --> 01:00:38.432
Shit! The Cops!

554
01:00:40.032 --> 01:00:43.211
- Dad. I have to stop.
- No. I just shot one of them. now go!

555
01:00:51.409 --> 01:00:52.609
Come on. go!

556
01:01:15.333 --> 01:01:16.136
Go right!

557
01:01:21.681 --> 01:01:22.811
Back. back. back!

558
01:01:24.100 --> 01:01:24.870
Come on. move!

559
01:01:28.239 --> 01:01:29.049
Come on. Kim.

560
01:01:37.137 --> 01:01:38.587
Go! Go!

561
01:01:44.427 --> 01:01:45.643
Come on. keep going!

562
01:01:58.041 --> 01:01:58.875
Left!

563
01:01:59.241 --> 01:01:59.741
Yes.

564
01:02:05.949 --> 01:02:06.759
Keep going!

565
01:02:10.008 --> 01:02:12.658
- Oh. no. they're shooting.
- Stay low. keep going.

566
01:02:17.116 --> 01:02:18.686
- Come on. faster.
- I can't!

567
01:02:18.926 --> 01:02:20.116
- Do it!
- I can't!

568
01:02:22.095 --> 01:02:24.126
Come on. move! Move!

569
01:02:24.674 --> 01:02:27.339
- Dad!
- Keep going! Watch the road!

570
01:02:28.793 --> 01:02:29.793
Right!

571
01:02:42.380 --> 01:02:43.440
Oh. shit!

572
01:03:09.213 --> 01:03:10.602
Come on. Kim. move!

573
01:03:14.461 --> 01:03:15.621
- Go! - Okay! - Go!

574
01:03:24.059 --> 01:03:25.129
C'mon! Keep going!

575
01:03:27.828 --> 01:03:28.848
Come on!

576
01:03:37.655 --> 01:03:38.785
Shit!

577
01:03:40.275 --> 01:03:42.914
- Dad!
- Keep going. stay low!

578
01:03:55.910 --> 01:03:57.770
- Faster. Kim.
- I can't!

579
01:04:03.128 --> 01:04:04.588
- Come on. faster!
- Dad!

580
01:04:04.808 --> 01:04:05.608
Keep going!

581
01:04:09.847 --> 01:04:10.716
You can make it!

582
01:04:12.126 --> 01:04:13.086
Do it.

583
01:04:36.810 --> 01:04:39.829
- Here. Don't stop!
- But there's soldiers.

584
01:04:40.069 --> 01:04:41.019
They'll move!

585
01:04:43.738 --> 01:04:44.718
Down. Kim!

586
01:05:11.131 --> 01:05:14.280
- Are you okay?
- Yeah.

587
01:05:17.679 --> 01:05:19.038
Keep your head down. Kimmy.

588
01:05:27.156 --> 01:05:27.756
Hey. Bry.

589
01:05:28.026 --> 01:05:31.175
<i>Sam. we're in the courtyard of
the U.S. embassy in Istanbul</i>

590
01:05:31.435 --> 01:05:32.695
with a smashed-up car.

591
01:05:33.145 --> 01:05:34.552
<i>Don't ask. Can you</i>

592
01:05:34.650 --> 01:05:36.554
call someone to make
sure we don't get shot?

593
01:05:36.774 --> 01:05:38.013
Yeah. of course.

594
01:05:38.014 --> 01:05:39.253
<i>Thanks.</i>

595
01:05:39.563 --> 01:05:41.703
It's Bry. he's in trouble in Istanbul.

596
01:05:44.312 --> 01:05:46.281
Mom didn't get away. did she?

597
01:05:48.731 --> 01:05:51.590
- No.
- Oh. God. Dad.

598
01:05:52.000 --> 01:05:54.749
- Tell me the truth. is she...?
- No. no. no. no. Kim.

599
01:05:55.069 --> 01:05:56.419
No. no she's not.

600
01:05:57.078 --> 01:06:00.018
But they have her.

601
01:06:00.388 --> 01:06:03.437
And they will use her until
they get what they want.

602
01:06:05.106 --> 01:06:06.036
Me!

603
01:06:08.006 --> 01:06:11.195
You'll be safe here in the
embassy until I come back.

604
01:06:11.935 --> 01:06:16.243
- Kimmy. it's gonna be okay.
- Dad. it's okay.

605
01:06:17.123 --> 01:06:18.813
Kim. Kim listen.

606
01:06:21.062 --> 01:06:23.022
I have to find them.

607
01:06:23.851 --> 01:06:25.371
and bring your mom back.

608
01:06:25.751 --> 01:06:30.126
And then I have to make sure these
people never bother us again in our lives.

609
01:06:30.710 --> 01:06:32.089
What are you gonna do?

610
01:06:36.518 --> 01:06:38.018
What I do best.

611
01:07:10.179 --> 01:07:11.629
Mrs. Mills.

612
01:07:13.128 --> 01:07:16.168
What should I do with you. Mrs. Mills?

613
01:07:44.510 --> 01:07:46.740
I have nothing against you.

614
01:07:47.009 --> 01:07:48.869
You didn't kill my son.

615
01:07:53.148 --> 01:07:55.297
But your husband did.

616
01:07:57.917 --> 01:07:59.846
Now he betrayed you.

617
01:08:00.096 --> 01:08:03.595
by choosing to save your daughter.
instead of you.

618
01:08:04.895 --> 01:08:07.734
He left you here like a dog.

619
01:08:09.064 --> 01:08:12.773
At least my daughter is still alive.

620
01:08:24.919 --> 01:08:26.379
Mrs. Mills.

621
01:08:26.689 --> 01:08:28.419
you are a good mother.

622
01:08:29.598 --> 01:08:32.088
and a brave woman.

623
01:08:32.977 --> 01:08:35.797
For that. I'm going to send you back home...

624
01:08:37.036 --> 01:08:38.926
piece by piece.

625
01:12:05.121 --> 01:12:08.363
Boris. shut the dog up!

626
01:12:24.686 --> 01:12:26.046
Go and see what happened.

627
01:12:35.383 --> 01:12:37.983
Let's go! Move her here to the Hammond.

628
01:12:38.253 --> 01:12:40.012
Quick. quick!

629
01:13:48.134 --> 01:13:49.344
You stay here.

630
01:14:55.876 --> 01:14:57.056
Go!

631
01:14:57.506 --> 01:14:59.026
Come on!

632
01:15:35.156 --> 01:15:36.336
Get lost!

633
01:16:26.523 --> 01:16:27.322
Honey?

634
01:18:54.623 --> 01:18:56.103
I'm here. Baby. I'm here.

635
01:18:56.673 --> 01:19:00.828
I'm coming back. Leny. I'm coming back.
Okay.

636
01:19:39.842 --> 01:19:41.361
What are you waiting for?

637
01:19:42.881 --> 01:19:47.250
- You have other sons?
- Two.

638
01:19:47.530 --> 01:19:52.478
And if I killed you. they will
come and seek revenge.

639
01:19:52.968 --> 01:19:55.307
They will for sure.

640
01:19:55.587 --> 01:19:57.337
And I will kill them. too.

641
01:19:58.577 --> 01:20:00.586
You can change that.

642
01:20:01.186 --> 01:20:04.235
You can go home. live your life.

643
01:20:04.575 --> 01:20:07.194
enjoy your sons. your grandsons.

644
01:20:08.764 --> 01:20:12.883
But my other son. Marko.

645
01:20:16.302 --> 01:20:18.671
the son you killed...

646
01:20:19.571 --> 01:20:22.630
am I supposed just to forget it?

647
01:20:22.880 --> 01:20:25.230
No. you'll just have to live with it.

648
01:20:25.889 --> 01:20:28.609
like the parents of all those kidnapped girls.

649
01:20:29.708 --> 01:20:32.708
or you can die... here.

650
01:20:32.958 --> 01:20:35.737
- What are you telling me?
- What I'm saying is...

651
01:20:36.537 --> 01:20:38.476
if you give me your word.

652
01:20:39.866 --> 01:20:43.215
I will throw-down this gun.
and simply walk away.

653
01:20:46.644 --> 01:20:48.204
Why?

654
01:20:48.563 --> 01:20:51.903
Because I'm tired of it all.

655
01:22:00.994 --> 01:22:03.054
Leny. I'm here.

656
01:22:03.884 --> 01:22:06.913
I'm here. baby. I'm here.
Come on.

657
01:22:12.961 --> 01:22:14.141
It's all right. Leny.

658
01:22:14.711 --> 01:22:16.110
It's okay.

659
01:22:19.389 --> 01:22:20.499
We're safe.

660
01:22:23.476 --> 01:22:24.176
Bryan?

661
01:22:25.890 --> 01:22:29.627
- Kim? Kim?
- She's safe.

662
01:22:31.806 --> 01:22:33.106
She's safe.

663
01:22:43.463 --> 01:22:44.993
We're all safe.

664
01:22:53.035 --> 01:22:53.035
Three weeks after

665
01:23:14.825 --> 01:23:16.644
Line it up!

666
01:23:17.954 --> 01:23:19.154
That's it!

667
01:23:21.693 --> 01:23:25.702
Now. begin to cut! Not too fast. Not so fast.

668
01:23:27.372 --> 01:23:30.391
Straighten it out! Straighten! Straighten!

669
01:23:33.580 --> 01:23:34.380
Stop. stop stop!

670
01:23:36.129 --> 01:23:36.999
Perfect.

671
01:23:53.175 --> 01:23:56.884
- Well... perfect score.
- Great!

672
01:23:58.673 --> 01:24:01.483
- Congratulations.
- Thank you. Thank you.

673
01:24:05.322 --> 01:24:06.321
I was perfect.

674
01:24:08.201 --> 01:24:12.410
I've been saying that since the day you were born.
Congratulations!

675
01:24:13.469 --> 01:24:16.739
So... what would you like to do to celebrate?

676
01:24:18.728 --> 01:24:20.917
- I think I have an idea.
- Yeah?

677
01:24:21.217 --> 01:24:23.667
- Yeah. I'll drive.
- Of course!

678
01:24:45.671 --> 01:24:49.110
Here you go! 3 double chocolate fudge.

679
01:24:50.540 --> 01:24:52.519
- Thank you.
- And who's having the strawberry?

680
01:24:52.769 --> 01:24:54.409
I'm sorry. but I just ordered 3.

681
01:24:54.429 --> 01:24:56.608
Well. actually the order said 4.

682
01:24:56.908 --> 01:24:59.737
- I ordered a 4th one.
- Yeah? For who?

683
01:25:01.957 --> 01:25:04.526
- Oh. Jamie. Hey.
- Hey.

684
01:25:05.056 --> 01:25:07.485
- Hi.
- Hi! Pretty good timing.

685
01:25:07.585 --> 01:25:08.205
Jamie.

686
01:25:09.185 --> 01:25:12.044
- It's cool if he joins us. right?
- Of course he can. Kim.

687
01:25:12.404 --> 01:25:13.674
Dad?

688
01:25:14.803 --> 01:25:16.767
- Right?
- Of course it is. Honey.

689
01:25:16.854 --> 01:25:17.554
Behave!

690
01:25:17.602 --> 01:25:19.372
It's nice to see you again. Sir.

691
01:25:20.212 --> 01:25:22.081
Nice to see you. too. Sit down.

692
01:25:23.721 --> 01:25:24.381
Hi.

693
01:25:24.481 --> 01:25:27.021
- We got you a strawberry.
- Oh. please.

694
01:25:27.040 --> 01:25:31.049
Thanks. Dad.
Do not shoot this one. I really like him.
